title: For Sale:  S&W NYSP Model 520 1980 Contract Revolver RARE and PRISTINE
postcontent:
This is a fine example of a RARE N Frame Smith & Wesson in .357 Magnum.

Smith & Wesson produced this revolver for the New York State Police in 1980.  NYSP went a different direction, cancelled the order, and Smith sold the revolvers on the civilian market.  Only 3000 were made.  To this day, the original 520 remains the ONLY fixed-sight N-Frame revolver Smith ever made in .357 Magnum.

This is a beautiful gun that you just don't come across often.  In this condition with box and papers, these guns sell well north of $1,000.  Mine has no box and paper, and is priced accordingly.  

Here is the deal guys, I have been screwed by a couple of guys on here in the past who say they are going to buy, and I hold the gun for them, turn other offers away, and then never hear from the buyer, or he doesn't have all the money, or he wants to trade his Hi-point or whatever.  So, this gun is NOT for trade.  Do not offer to trade me.  I am selling to the first guy with Hundred Dollar Bills, no matter what.  You want the gun, be prepared to meet to close the sale. HK45 models can be also be fitted with threaded barrels for use with muzzle mounted sound suppressors.

Each HK45 comes standard with an extra backstrap; medium and small interchangeable backstraps ensure an optimal fit for most shooterâ€™s hands and complement the ergonomic profile grip.

An improved USP-style control lever a combination safety and decocking lever is frame mounted on the HK45 and is quickly accessible. The HK45 control lever has a positive stop and returns to the â€˜fireâ€™ position after decocking.

By using the modular approach to the internal components first pioneered by HK on the USP the control lever function of the HK45 can be switched from the left to the right side of the pistol to accommodate left-handed shooters (additional parts required). Left and right mounted control levers provide safety and/or decocking functions as required and can be fitted to the pistol simply by changing parts. For true ambidextrous use a control lever can also be mounted on both sides of the pistol if required.

Well-suited for personal defense use the HK45 is available in or can be converted to a wide variety of variants that use different trigger firing modes including double action/single action (DA/SA) and DAO (double action only). The DAO mode uses the unique Heckler & Koch LEM (Law Enforcement Modification) firing system for improved double action trigger pull.
